00:00:23:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:23:150000.Dialogue: Yes, Infinite Sheldon defeats all other cards and does not violate the rule against homemade cards because I made it at work.

00:00:32:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:32:070000.Dialogue: Do you understand why people don't want to play with you?

00:00:35:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:35:160000.Dialogue: No... although it's a question I've been pondering since preschool.

00:00:45:110000.Speaker: Penny
00:00:45:110000.Dialogue: Hey, your copy of Science magazine was in my mailbox.

00:00:49:080000.Speaker: Zack
00:00:49:080000.Dialogue: Check it out-- all about planets this month.

00:00:54:110000.Speaker: Zack
00:00:54:110000.Dialogue: Agree to disagree. That's what I love about science-- there's no one right answer.

00:01:05:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:05:050000.Dialogue: So... you and Zack again, huh?

00:01:08:200000.Speaker: Penny
00:01:08:200000.Dialogue: Yeah, yeah, me and Zack again.

00:01:13:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:01:13:220000.Dialogue: Okay, we should, we should go.

00:01:15:050000.Speaker: Zack
00:01:15:050000.Dialogue: Ah, not yet. I want to talk science with the science dudes.

00:01:18:150000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:18:150000.Dialogue: Oh, and the science dudes want to talk science with you.

00:01:23:190000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:23:190000.Dialogue: What do you want to talk about-- rocks, dinosaurs, our friend the beaver?

00:01:30:040000.Speaker: Zack
00:01:30:040000.Dialogue: You know, I saw this great thing on the Discovery Channel. Turns out that if you kill a starfish, it'll just come back to life.

00:01:38:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:38:090000.Dialogue: Was the starfish wearing boxer shorts? Because you might have been watching Nickelodeon.

00:01:45:110000.Speaker: Zack
00:01:45:110000.Dialogue: No, I'm almost sure that it was the Discovery Channel. It was a great show. They also said dolphins might be smarter than people.

00:01:52:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:52:080000.Dialogue: They might be smarter than some people.

00:01:58:020000.Speaker: Zack
00:01:58:020000.Dialogue: Maybe we can do an experiment to find out.

00:02:00:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:00:160000.Dialogue: That's easy enough. We'd need a large tank of water, a hoop to jump through, and a bucket of whatever bite-sized treats you find tasty.

00:02:22:200000.Speaker: Zack
00:02:22:200000.Dialogue: Oh, I see. You guys are inferring that I'm stupid.

00:02:26:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:26:080000.Dialogue: That's not correct. We were implying it. You then inferred it.

00:02:39:120000.Speaker: Penny
00:02:39:120000.Dialogue: You know, for a group of guys who claim they spent most of their lives being bullied, you can be real jerks. Shame on all of you.

00:02:49:230000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:49:230000.Dialogue: What the hell did I do?

00:03:21:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:21:200000.Dialogue: Do you think Penny's right? Were we bullying Zack?

00:03:24:110000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:24:110000.Dialogue: No, I know bullying. He left here unswirlied and his ass crack was underpants-free.

00:03:31:070000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:31:070000.Dialogue: And nobody drew a penis on his forehead.

00:03:37:160000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:37:160000.Dialogue: First day of cricket camp. They drew it so the testicles were my eyes.

00:03:47:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:47:030000.Dialogue: I don't know, I think we might owe the guy an apology.

00:03:52:050000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:52:050000.Dialogue: You started it, we just piled on.

00:04:05:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:05:010000.Dialogue: Yeah, Milk Duds, with their self-deprecating name and remarkably mild flavor, are the most apologetic of the boxed candies.

00:04:15:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:15:070000.Dialogue: I got a better idea. We're all responsible. I say we all go.

00:04:22:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:22:130000.Dialogue: Come on, who's with me? Free comic books to anyone who comes with me. I might get punched. You really want to miss that?

00:04:57:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:57:030000.Dialogue: Listen, the stuff we were saying before-- we were just kidding around.

00:05:01:040000.Scene: At Penny’s door. Leonard knocks three times.
00:05:01:040000.Speaker: Zack
00:05:01:040000.Dialogue: No, you weren't. You were making fun of me.

00:05:03:180000.Scene: At Penny’s door. Leonard knocks three times.
00:05:03:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:03:180000.Dialogue: Come on, that's what we do. We give each other a hard time. Hey, Sheldon, you look like a praying mantis.

00:05:11:200000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:05:13:190000.Speaker: Leonard

00:05:16:020000.Scene: At Penny’s door. Leonard knocks three times.
00:05:16:020000.Speaker: Zack
00:05:16:020000.Dialogue: I don't know, it still wasn't very nice.

00:05:31:130000.Speaker: Zack
00:05:31:130000.Dialogue: You guys want to come in and have a beer?

00:05:33:030000.Scene: At Penny’s door. Leonard knocks three times.
00:05:33:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:33:030000.Dialogue: Uh, we're on our way to the comic book store.

00:05:34:220000.Scene: At Penny’s door. Leonard knocks three times.
00:05:34:220000.Speaker: Howard

00:05:36:150000.Scene: At Penny’s door. Leonard knocks three times.
00:05:36:150000.Speaker: Zack
00:05:36:150000.Dialogue: Really? I haven't been to a comic book store in literally a million years.

00:05:59:230000.Speaker: Zack

00:06:05:040000.Speaker: Zack
00:06:05:040000.Dialogue: Wow, this place is awesome. Where do they keep the Archies?

00:06:09:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:09:130000.Dialogue: In the bedrooms of ten-year- old girls, where they belong.

00:06:12:220000.Speaker: Zack
00:06:12:220000.Dialogue: Oh, no, you're thinking old-school Archie. It's much more sophisticated now. Like, there's two universes, and Archie's married to Betty in one and Veronica in the other. Midge is even breaking up with Moose.

00:06:34:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:34:030000.Dialogue: Uh, no. Oh, this is Zack. He's a friend of ours. Zack, this is Stuart. He owns the store.

00:06:41:100000.Speaker: Stuart
00:06:41:100000.Dialogue: Yeah, I work 70 hours a week and average $1.65 an hour.

00:06:52:130000.Speaker: Howard
00:06:52:130000.Dialogue: No, it's an indictment of the American education system.

00:07:02:110000.Speaker: Stuart
00:07:02:110000.Dialogue: So are you guys coming to my New Year's Eve costume party?

00:07:05:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:05:100000.Dialogue: Of course. We're coming as the Justice League of America.

00:07:08:170000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:08:170000.Dialogue: Switching it up from last year when we came as the Justice League of America.

00:07:12:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:12:180000.Dialogue: To that point, it occurs to me that we might have an opportunity to finally snare Best Group Costume if we shore up our weak link, which is clearly Leonard as Superman.

00:07:26:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:26:080000.Dialogue: Hey, I got new boots this year. Guaranteed to add three inches.

00:07:36:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:36:090000.Dialogue: Is there anyone we know who would make a more manly and convincing son of Krypton?

00:07:52:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:52:080000.Dialogue: I was thinking specifically of the gentleman over there moving his lips as he enjoys the latest exploits of Betty and Veronica.

00:08:05:180000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:05:180000.Dialogue: He is the only person we know with actual muscles.

00:08:09:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:09:100000.Dialogue: You can't replace me with Zack.

00:08:15:060000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:15:060000.Dialogue: Yeah, she seems happier. Why wouldn't we be?

00:08:18:140000.Speaker: Zack
00:08:18:140000.Dialogue: Score. I got an Archie, Betty and Veronica, and a Jughead. All set for my weekend number twos.

00:08:27:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:27:070000.Dialogue: Congratulations. Zack, how would you like to be Superman?

00:08:33:020000.Speaker: Zack
00:08:33:020000.Dialogue: I don't know, sounds like a lot of responsibility.

00:08:40:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:40:130000.Dialogue: Fine, if Zack's going to be Superman, I want to be Green Lantern.

00:08:46:030000.Speaker: Raj
00:08:46:030000.Dialogue: I don't want to be Aquaman. He sucks.

00:08:56:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:56:140000.Dialogue: Excuse me, I believe Aquaman uses his telepathic powers to request the fish do their business elsewhere.

00:09:08:040000.Speaker: Zack
00:09:08:040000.Dialogue: Well, you won't be when you hear the great news.

00:09:11:060000.Speaker: Zack
00:09:11:060000.Dialogue: We're going to a costume party at the comic book store on New Year's Eve, and you get to be Wonder Woman.

00:09:19:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:19:090000.Dialogue: Complete with bulletproof bracelets and lasso of truth.

00:09:26:120000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:26:120000.Dialogue: Wait, why me? Wh-Why can't your girlfriend be Wonder Woman?

00:09:29:180000.Speaker: Howard
00:09:29:180000.Dialogue: She and her lab team are under quarantine. Seems at the Christmas party they were doing Jell-O shots out of petri dishes that used to contain yellow fever.

00:09:40:050000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:40:050000.Dialogue: Okay, what about your friend Amy?

00:09:42:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:42:230000.Dialogue: Amy Farrah Fowler doesn't believe in wearing costumes. She isn't the free spirit I am.

00:09:51:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:51:170000.Dialogue: Okay, well, forget it. I'm not spending my New Year's Eve at a comic book store wearing a Wonder Woman costume.

00:09:59:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:09:59:070000.Dialogue: He says he'll wear it if you'll be Aquaman.

00:10:16:050000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:10:16:050000.Speaker: Leonard

00:10:18:060000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:10:18:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:18:060000.Dialogue: We're going to be late. I'm pacing nervously.

00:10:22:040000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:10:22:040000.Speaker: Leonard

00:10:23:100000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:10:23:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:23:100000.Dialogue: This is how the Flash paces.

00:10:26:180000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:10:26:180000.Speaker: Leonard

00:10:29:100000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:10:29:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:29:100000.Dialogue: I'm not Sheldon. I'm the Flash. And now I'm going to the Grand Canyon to scream in frustration. I'm back.

00:10:40:010000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:10:40:010000.Speaker: Howard

00:10:44:010000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:10:44:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:44:010000.Dialogue: Oh, I hardly think so. The real caped crusader calls his crime-fighting cohorts when he's running late.

00:10:49:020000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:10:49:020000.Speaker: Howard
00:10:49:020000.Dialogue: I had to walk. I couldn't get Raj on the back of my scooter.

00:11:02:100000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:11:02:100000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:02:100000.Dialogue: I've said this before, and I'll say it again. Aquaman sucks.

00:11:07:140000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:11:07:140000.Speaker: Zack
00:11:07:140000.Dialogue: Look up in the sky. It's a bird. It's a plane. I forget the rest.

00:11:15:210000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:11:15:210000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:15:210000.Dialogue: All right. Let's get this thing over with.

00:11:19:170000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:11:19:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:19:170000.Dialogue: I'm sorry. But in what universe is Wonder Woman blonde?

00:11:24:060000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:11:24:060000.Speaker: Howard
00:11:24:060000.Dialogue: Relax. No one's going to be looking at her hair.

00:11:29:150000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:11:29:150000.Speaker: Howard

00:11:33:070000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:11:33:070000.Speaker: Howard

00:11:37:130000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:11:37:130000.Speaker: Zack
00:11:37:130000.Dialogue: Hold on. The costume came with a black wig. Where is it, babe?

00:11:39:190000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:11:39:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:39:190000.Dialogue: No. I'm not wearing it. It looks stupid.

00:11:41:200000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:11:41:200000.Speaker: Zack
00:11:41:200000.Dialogue: Come on. We're trying to win a contest here.

00:11:43:100000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:11:43:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:43:100000.Dialogue: Forget it. I'm not wearing the wig.

00:11:44:160000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:11:44:160000.Speaker: Zack

00:11:50:110000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:11:50:110000.Speaker: Howard

00:11:53:080000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:11:53:080000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:11:55:210000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:11:55:210000.Speaker: Zack
00:11:55:210000.Dialogue: Okay, babe. Uh... Kind of embarrassing me in front of my friends.

00:12:00:220000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:12:00:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:00:220000.Dialogue: Okay. You know what? I changed my mind. I'm not going.

00:12:06:000000.Scene: The apartment. Leonard is dressed as Green Lantern, Sheldon as The Flash.
00:12:06:000000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:06:000000.Dialogue: Looks like someone else is going to have to be Wonder Woman.

00:12:18:080000.Speaker: Zack
00:12:18:080000.Dialogue: Then who are you talking to?

00:12:26:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:26:120000.Dialogue: Penny, Penny, Penny, Penny, Penny, Penny, Penny, Penny, Penny, Penny, Penny, Penny, Penny, Penny, Penny, Penny, Penny, Penny Penny, Penny...

00:12:34:180000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:34:180000.Dialogue: What the hell is wrong with you?

00:12:37:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:37:170000.Dialogue: I'm the Flash. I just knocked 30,000 times.

00:12:40:140000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:40:140000.Dialogue: Okay. What do you want, Sheldon?

00:12:46:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:46:230000.Dialogue: Yes. You're afraid that costume makes you look fat.

00:12:58:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:58:040000.Dialogue: Don't worry. Wonder Woman was an Amazon. And Amazons tend to be very beefy gals.

00:13:12:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:12:140000.Dialogue: But they're not blonde, so put on your wig.

00:13:35:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:35:220000.Dialogue: If it makes you feel any better, when I was dating Penny, she used to flip out on me all the time.

00:13:45:170000.Speaker: Zack
00:13:45:170000.Dialogue: She told me she dated a guy named Leonard. Who would have thought it was you?

00:13:52:180000.Speaker: Zack
00:13:52:180000.Dialogue: I don't know. Somebody bigger and... Yeah, sure. Why not you?

00:14:04:020000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:04:020000.Dialogue: Okay, I guess we just go without a Wonder Woman.

00:14:07:180000.Speaker: Zack
00:14:07:180000.Dialogue: I don't want to go without Penny.

00:14:09:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:09:020000.Dialogue: Oh, great. No Superman, no Wonder Woman? All we've got is a skinny Flash, an Indian Aquaman, a nearsighted Green Lantern, and a teeny, tiny Dark Knight.

00:14:21:150000.Speaker: Laughing
00:14:21:150000.Dialogue: Obviously, we're no longer a Justice League.

00:14:25:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:25:090000.Dialogue: We have no choice but to switch to our Muppet Baby costumes.

00:14:35:110000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:35:110000.Dialogue: Oh, man. Scooter sucks. He's the Aquaman of the Muppet Babies.

00:14:44:030000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:44:030000.Dialogue: No, we can still make this work. Leonard, you talk to Penny.

00:14:47:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:47:230000.Dialogue: What makes you think I can convince her?

00:14:49:230000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:49:230000.Dialogue: You got her to have sex with you. Obviously, your superpower is brainwashing.

00:14:57:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:57:170000.Dialogue: Okay, let me see if I understand this. You want me to convince my ex-girlfriend to go to a costume party with her new boyfriend just so we can win a stupid prize?

00:15:07:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:07:200000.Dialogue: Yes. And make her wear the black wig. Good luck.

00:15:19:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:19:080000.Dialogue: Come on, let me just talk to you.

00:15:25:140000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:25:140000.Dialogue: I'm not going to that party, Leonard.

00:15:27:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:27:080000.Dialogue: Okay, listen. You don't have to wear the wig. At this party, we're gonna win first prize just by showing up with a girl.

00:15:37:000000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:37:000000.Dialogue: Did I do something? I mean, I tried to be friends with Zack, like you said, which believe me, was difficult, given how you and me used to be... you know, "you and me," and now you and him are "you and him."

00:15:49:110000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:49:110000.Dialogue: Okay, look. We're not really "me and him."

00:15:54:060000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:54:060000.Dialogue: I don't know. I only started seeing Zack again so I wouldn't be alone on New Year's Eve. How pathetic is that?

00:16:02:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:02:170000.Dialogue: Not as pathetic as dressing up like this and going to a comic book store on New Year's Eve.

00:16:08:080000.Speaker: Penny
00:16:08:080000.Dialogue: You make a cute Green Arrow.

00:16:21:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:21:040000.Dialogue: There's a big difference. Arrow. Lantern.

00:16:30:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:16:30:020000.Dialogue: Whatever. Look, if Zack and I had just gone to a regular club or a party, it would have been fine, but this, with the costumes, and you...

00:16:40:040000.Speaker: Penny
00:16:40:040000.Dialogue: Nothing. Let's go to the party. How do I look?

00:16:52:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:52:180000.Dialogue: Um... I guarantee you'll be the prettiest girl there.

00:16:57:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:16:57:200000.Dialogue: Okay, the good news is, we have a Wonder Woman.

00:17:03:100000.Speaker: Howard
00:17:03:100000.Dialogue: Superman probably isn't getting laid tonight.

00:17:12:160000.Speaker: Stuart
00:17:12:160000.Dialogue: And the award for best group costume goes to... Justice League of America...

00:17:30:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:30:060000.Dialogue: Thank you! Thank you so much!

00:17:33:090000.Speaker: Stuart
00:17:33:090000.Dialogue: Okay. Okay, ten seconds to midnight.

00:17:37:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:37:090000.Dialogue: No, wait! I have a speech.

00:18:00:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:00:050000.Dialogue: I'm not going to say another word until you people settle down. I'm waiting.

00:18:13:010000.Speaker: Zack
00:18:13:010000.Dialogue: That was a great party. We should dress like this all the time.

00:18:26:080000.Speaker: Howard
00:18:26:080000.Dialogue: Check it out. Those guys are breaking into that car.

00:18:32:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:32:010000.Dialogue: We're the Justice League of America. There's only one thing we can do. Turn around and slowly walk away.

00:18:55:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:55:180000.Dialogue: Look, I know our winter thermostat setting is 72 degrees, but I'm a little warm, so I'm going to turn it down.

00:19:25:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:25:100000.Dialogue: Good Lord, how you frustrate me, Leonard Hofstadter!
